{"lemma":"فَجِّ","slug":"فَجِّ","root":"ف.ج.ج","root_slug":"ف-ج-ج","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ج-ج","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فَجّ","root":"فجج","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33015","n33019","n33020"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wide mountain pass"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"gorge, pass, defile"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33015","headword_ar":"فَجَّ","root":"fj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [see. pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajijota","text_ar":"فَجِجْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yafaj~u","text_ar":"يَفَجُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajajN","text_ar":"فَجَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * O, * K, * TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He had the feet wide apart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, said of a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he had the knees wide apart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and, said of a beast, or quadruped,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he had the hocks wide apart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajajN","text_ar":"فَجَجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is more ugly than what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faHajN","text_ar":"فَحَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O, K.) ―         -b2-  See also 7. ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faj~a rijolayohi","text_ar":"فَجَّ رِجْلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faj~a maA","text_ar":"فَجَّ مَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayona rijolayohi","text_ar":"بَيْنَ رِجْلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yafuj~u","text_ar":"يَفُجُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faj~N","text_ar":"فَجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He opened"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"parted"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his legs"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"widely;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he straddled;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Afj~","text_ar":"افجّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Afj~ rijolayohi","text_ar":"افجّ رِجْلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he parted his legs widely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a man and of a beast; (O;) so too ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fAj~","text_ar":"فاجّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[alone], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajaA","text_ar":"فَجَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and one says also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tfAj~","text_ar":"تفاجّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning the same], of one walking, (S, K, TA,) and meaning he did thus to make water, (Mgh, TA,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fAj~","text_ar":"فاجّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fijaAjN","text_ar":"فِجَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mufaAj~apN","text_ar":"مُفَاجَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", both of these verbs said of a man; but ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tfAj~","text_ar":"تفاجّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he parted his legs very widely;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tfAj~t","text_ar":"تفاجّت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said of a she-camel, (A, O,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liloHalobi","text_ar":"لِلْحَلْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be milked"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (A;) and of a sheep or goat ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAp","text_ar":"شَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (O.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA yabuwlu","text_ar":"وَلَا يَبُولُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA $aYo'N yufaAj~u","text_ar":"مَا شَىْءٌ يُفَاجُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is a thing that straddles and will not make water?"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is an enigma: it is a thing like a couch, having four legs. (A, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfaj~u","text_ar":"الفَجُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the language of the Arabs is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The making an opening,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"interval,"},{"kind":"text","text":"between two things. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajajotu","text_ar":"فَجَجْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqawosa","text_ar":"القَوْسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afuj~uhaA","text_ar":"اَفُجُّهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faj~N","text_ar":"فَجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I raised the string of the bow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to make it distant"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabid","text_ar":"كَبِد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; (S, O, K;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajawotuhaA","text_ar":"فَجَوْتُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faj~a AlA^aroDa","text_ar":"فَجَّ الاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the O,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlArDa","text_ar":"الارضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Afj~","text_ar":"افجّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He clave the ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"with the plough,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a manner not approved."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faj~a","text_ar":"فَجَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a horse &c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He purposed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desired, to run."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajaAjapN","text_ar":"فَجَاجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["TA","S","O","K","Mgh","A"]},{"entry_id":"n33019","headword_ar":"فَجٌّ","root":"fj","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wide road between two mountains;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fujaAjN","text_ar":"فُجَاجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (O, K:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a mountain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, TA:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the anterior part of a mountain, wider than a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iEob","text_ar":"شِعْب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a depressed road:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a conspicuous and wide road:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a far-extending beaten track or road:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, TA: [see an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EimoqN","text_ar":"عِمْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or, accord. to ISh, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a track"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though it were a road;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a road between two mountains,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having on either side what is termed a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^ow","text_ar":"فَاْو"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a word variously explained], (so in the L,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between two walls"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAy^iTayoni","text_ar":"حَايِطَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (so in the TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and extending to the distance of two days' journey,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"three, if a road"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not a road;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"if a road, abounding with herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA:) pl. [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fijaAjN","text_ar":"فِجَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, S, O, Msb) and [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afij~apN","text_ar":"اَفِجَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is extr. [with respect to analogy], (Th, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afuj~N","text_ar":"اَفُجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.)       -A2-  See also the next paragraph, in two places."}],"source_refs":["O","K","AHeyth","TA","Th","Msb","L","S"]},{"entry_id":"n33020","headword_ar":"فِجٌّ","root":"fj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Syrian"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biT~iyx","text_ar":"بِطِّيخ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"melon"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water-melon"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, A, O, K,) which the Persians call the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Indian."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fij~N","text_ar":"فِجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the S and A and K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faj~N","text_ar":"فَجٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (thus in the O, and by implication in the Msb, [and thus pronounced in the present day,]) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Unripe;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, Msb, K;) applied to fruit (A, Msb, K) of any kind, (A,) &c; (Msb;) to anything of melons ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biT~iyx","text_ar":"بِطِّيخ"},{"kind":"text","text":") and of other fruits; (S, O;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajaAjapN","text_ar":"فَجَاجَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, K;) but ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faj~N","text_ar":"فَجٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajaAjapN","text_ar":"فَجَاجَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"are not mentioned by Ed-Deenawaree [i. e. AHn; and the latter (which see below) I think doubtful in the sense expl. above]. (O.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","O","K","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}